                <div class="menu-right col-xs-8 ">
                    <h2>Data Policy</h2>
                    <p>The quality and professionally processed data enable cities to create more informed and effective decisions, to evaluate their activities, to respond faster and more directly to the needs of their citizens, which can positively influence public finances and simultaneously improve the living conditions of the citizens. For the purposes of public knowledge, the data represent an information source about the activities of city allowing citizens to deduce responsibilities towards the elected representatives. For the business and non-governmental sector, data represent an instrument for improving quality of provided services.</p>

                    <h3>Important links:</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Basic principles and priorities of the Data Policy of the Capital City of SR Bratislava<br><span class="right-text-link"><a href="{$basePath}/pdf/zppdphmsrba_en.pdf" target="_blank">Download in PDF</a></span></li>
                        <li>OpenData Bratislava<br><span class="right-text-link"><a href="https://github.com/magistrat-bratislava/opendata" target="_blank">https://github.com/magistrat-bratislava/opendata</a></span></li>
                    </ul>

                    <h3>The Municipal Office of the Capital City of the Slovak Republic Bratislava Directive on Data Policy</h3>
                    <h3>Article I</h3>
                    <h4>Introductory Provisions</h4>
                    <ol>
                        <li>This Directive regulates the rules for the collection, generation, monitoring, sharing and manipulation of data sets (including geospatial data sets) and the process of publishing data on the open data portal of the Capital City of the Slovak Republic Bratislava.</li>
                        <li>The coordinator of data policy is the Department of Data Policy and Analysis (DDPA) under the Informatics and Data Policy Section of the Municipal Office of the Capital City of the Slovak Republic Bratislava and the Chief Innovation Officer. The coordination of geospatial data is in cooperation with the Department of Geographic Information System (DGIS) under the Informatics and Data Policy Section.</li>
                        <li>The Capital City of the Slovak Republic Bratislava evaluates the data collected and generated in its territory by public authorities and third parties. The Capital City of the Slovak Republic Bratislava seeks and establishes partnerships with third parties, in particular with public administration authorities, the business and academic sectors, city districts and the Higher Territorial Administrative Unit of Bratislava, in the area of generation, sharing and use of data. The main aims are effective exchange of information and data, unification of data standards and creation of opportunities for the use of data for the benefit of the inhabitants of the Capital City of the Slovak Republic Bratislava.</li>
                        <li>The Capital City of the Slovak Republic Bratislava introduces policies and measures enabling the implementation of data policy at all levels, ensuring technical and content interoperability of data, uniformity of formats and licenses, etc. (principle of “interoperability”).</li>
                        <li>The Capital City of the Slovak Republic Bratislava commits to adhere to the principles set out in the Declaration of Cities for Digital Rights.</li>
                        <li>In the course of data policy implementation, the Capital City of the Slovak Republic Bratislava respects the privacy of the citizens and adheres to the rules of the European Union on the protection of personal data, as well as national legislation.</li>
                    </ol>

                    <h3>Article II</h3>
                    <h4>Basic Terminology</h4>
                    <ol>
                        <li>A Data set is a set of data or information that is used by a computer application or system. The data or information in a data set may be in a structured or unstructured form and are stored in a machine-readable format.</li>
                        <li>Granularity (also level of detail) represents the level of depth of the data set representation. High granularity represents a high level of detail (individual data), low granularity represents a low level of detail (aggregate data).</li>
                        <li>An Item (also a variable or column) represents the vertical structure of a data set. It carries data or information often categorized by a valid codebook.</li>
                        <li>Open data - the standard for labelling data as open data is the provision of the data in a dataset with a quality of at least level 3 and in an open way for use, which is met only if the legal aspects of the data access and use are explicitly settled, if it is possible to establish legal relationships for the use of data by means of anonymous remote automatic access, if access to the data is granted to all persons under the same conditions and these conditions are explicitly stated, if the data can be used for both commercial and non-commercial purposes, if the data can be combined with other data, supplemented, corrected, modified, or used without the obligation to use other data from the dataset, and if the activities under point 4) are free of charge. Further standard for labelling data as open data is the Creative Commons CC0 or CC-BY licence to ensure the fulfilment of conditions and the provision of the dataset metadata in an open way. If the dataset contains at least one open data, it shall be referred to as an open data dataset (Article 52 (1) and (2) of Act No. 55/2014 Collection of Laws of the Slovak Republic).</li>
                        <li>The Open data portal is a web portal managed by the Informatics and Data Policy Section and designed for publishing and disseminating open data to the general public.</li>
                        <li>A Responsible body is any organisational unit of the Municipal Office of the Capital City of the Slovak Republic Bratislava, which is responsible for the generation and/or management of any data sets.</li>
                        <li>A Coordinator is an employee of the Municipal Office of the Capital City of the Slovak Republic Bratislava who is within his organisational unit (responsible body) responsible for the administration of data sets, their updating, the creation of an information minimum, the creation and administration of metadata and the communication with the DDPA.</li>
                        <li>HelpDesk represents the technical support services provided by the Informatics and Data Policy Section. The helpdesk.bratislava.sk application is pre-installed on every work computer available to the employees.</li>
                        <li>Keywords (also tags) are tags or labels that will be assigned to individual data sets on a dedicated portal to simplify the search for data sets. Keywords will be assigned to data sets to reflect their content or category to which they primarily or secondarily belong.</li>
                        <li>Metadata are structured data that provide information about data sets. They describe in more detail the data set, its characteristics, data types and scope, date of the last update or contact details of the coordinator (see e.g. Act No. 55/2014 Collection of Laws of the Slovak Republic).</li>
                        <li>Individual data represent data that describe entities or individuals individually and in a targeted manner. The entity or subject can be identified based on them.</li>
                        <li>Information minimum is a set of basic information about the data set. The difference between metadata and information minimum lies in their scope. Information minimum is a subset of the data set metadata.</li>
                        <li>The Format of a data set represents a predetermined layout of data in a document or file. It is also the method by which stored data are organised. The different formats differ in their internal structure, data ordering logic and size.</li>
                        <li>Aggregated data are the primary data aggregated into groups according to selected indicators.  Aggregation means grouping or merging multiple values into one. Aggregated data do not allow the identification of a particular entity or individual.</li>
                        <li>Protection of personal data is a summary of the rules on the treatment of personal data which belongs to the area of fundamental human rights. In the Slovak Republic, protection of personal data is governed by the Regulation 2016/679 of the European Parliament and of the Council of 27 April 2016 on the protection of natural persons to the processing of personal data and on the free movement of such data, and repealing Directive 95/46/ES (General Data Protection Regulation). </li>
                        <li>Shared storage represents a remote data storage accessible at any time to employees authorised by the administrator of the storage. Shared storage is used to share, manage and monitor available data sets, information minimum and metadata within the Municipal Office of the Capital City of the Slovak Republic Bratislava.</li>
                        <li>The Geospatial data catalogue is a map portal and data repository that enables geospatial information to be accessed and shared via WFS and WMS services according to the standard defined by the OGC. </li>
                        <li>A Municipal organisation is understood as a budgetary or allowance organisation established by the Capital City of Slovakia, a non-profit organisation of the Capital City of Slovakia Bratislava and a foundation of the Capital City of Slovakia Bratislava. </li>
                        <li>
                            A Municipal enterprise is a company in which the Capital City of SR Bratislava:
                            <ul>
                                <li>has a capital participation of more than 50%,</li>
                                <li>has a share of more than 50% of the voting rights,</li>
                                <li>has a decisive influence, </li>
                                <li>appoints or elects more than a half of the members of the management body.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li>A data set License represents the right to use the protected work (a data set) in an agreed manner. A more detailed regulation of the terms of use is usually contained in the license agreement or under the license agreement contained in another type of agreement.</li>
                    </ol>

                    <h3>Article III</h3>
                    <h4>Responsibilities of the Department of Data Policy and Analysis (DDPA)</h4>

                    <ol>
                        <li>
                            The Department is responsible for:
                            <ul>
                                <li>Creation, development and implementation of data policy of the Capital City of the Slovak Republic Bratislava in cooperation with key departments, including determination of data standards based on European and national data standards,</li>
                                <li>monitoring and auditing of data sets of the Municipal Office of the Capital City of the Slovak Republic Bratislava,</li>
                                <li>coordination of the organisational units and responsible bodies in the field of data policy,  </li>
                                <li>collecting and acquiring new data sources for the purposes of the DDPA,</li>
                                <li>the approval of data sets procurement plan, in the field of geospatial data sets in cooperation with the DGIS,</li>
                                <li>administration of the unified shared storage of the Municipal Office of the Capital City of the Slovak Republic Bratislava in cooperation with the Department of the Municipal Information System of the Informatics and Data Policy Section, </li>
                                <li>administration of access to the shared storage of the Municipal Office of the Capital City of the Slovak Republic Bratislava,</li>
                                <li>publication of open data on a dedicated portal,</li>
                                <li>creation of analyses, forecasts and projections as supporting information tools for the purposes of planning and decision-making of the Capital City of the Slovak Republic Bratislava, </li>
                                <li>coordination in the area of collection, processing and systematization of data sets within the Municipal Office of the Capital City of the Slovak Republic Bratislava, municipal organisations and municipal enterprises, in order to unify data collection and evaluation. </li>
                                <li>submitting an annual evaluation of the status of the data published by the responsible bodies to the Chief Innovation Officer.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                    </ol>

                    <h3>Article IV</h3>
                    <h4>Responsibilities of the Department of Geographic Information System</h4>

                    <ol>
                        <li>
                            The Department, in cooperation with the DDPA, is responsible for:
                            <ul>
                                <li>Creation, development and implementation of the development strategy of the geoinformation system of the Capital City of the Slovak Republic Bratislava, </li>
                                <li>monitoring and audit of the geoinformation data sets of the Municipal Office of the Capital City of the Slovak Republic Bratislava,</li>
                                <li>coordination of the organisational units and responsible bodies in the area of development of the geoinformation system of the Capital City of the Slovak Republic Bratislava, </li>
                                <li>collection of new geospatial data sets,  </li>
                                <li>publication of open data on a dedicated portal.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            The Department in cooperation with the Department of Municipal Information System (DMIS) is responsible for:
                            <ul>
                                <li>administration of the geospatial data catalogue of the Municipal Office of the Capital City of the Slovak Republic Bratislava.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                    </ol>

                    <h3>Article V</h3>
                    <h4>Responsibilities of Coordinators and Responsible Organisational Bodies</h4>

                    <ol>
                        <li>Responsible bodies maintain records of data sets they are in charge of and/or ensure their creation and/or management, </li>
                        <li>
                            Responsible bodies maintain information minimum on each data set in uniform format consisting of:
                            <ul>
                                <li>Name</li>
                                <li>Format</li>
                                <li>Owner</li>
                                <li>Licence</li>
                                <li>Size</li>
                                <li>Date of the last update</li>
                                <li>Regularity of update</li>
                                <li>Coordinator of the responsible body</li>
                                <li>Name of the responsible body</li>
                                <li>Keywords</li>
                                <li>Reasons for use</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li>Responsible bodies maintain a metadata questionnaire for each data set. A model of the metadata questionnaire is annex 1 of this Directive.</li>
                        <li>Responsible bodies and coordinators always cooperate with the DDPA on the acquisition, processing, systematization, storage and management of data sets.  </li>
                        <li>Responsible bodies create a plan of creation or procurement of data sets (including geospatial data sets) at least one year in advance. The data set procurement plan becomes effective upon approval by the DDPA and the Chief Innovation Officer. </li>
                        <li>
                            In the case of an intent to procure data sets or geospatial data sets which are not part of the procurement plan for the given year, a responsible body always asks for an approval:
                            <ul>
                                <li>of data sets from the DDPA and the Chief Innovation Officer,</li>
                                <li>of geospatial data sets from the DDPA, the Chief Innovation Officer and the DGIS.</li>
                            </ul>
                            If an approval has been given, the Department of the Public Procurement (DPP) can begin the process of public procurement. Without an explicit consent of the ODPA and the Chief Innovation with the procurement of the data sets, DPP is not permitted to start a public procurement.
                        </li>
                        <li>The coordinators of the individual organisational units update the information minimum and metadata questionnaire of the data sets they are in charge of regularly and timely and/or ensure their creation and/or manage them no later than one month from the date of the creation or last update of the data set,</li>
                        <li>The coordinators of the individual organisational bodies share data sets, including geospatial data sets, with DDPA in a predetermined shared storage regularly and timely, </li>
                        <li>The coordinators of the individual organisational bodies share geospatial data sets in the geospatial data catalogue,</li>
                        <li>The coordinators of the individual organisational bodies, together with the data sets, share the information minimum and the metadata questionnaire about each data set with DDPA, </li>
                        <li>In cooperation with DDPA, the coordinators and responsible organizational bodies ensure all activities related to the process of data processing and publishing on the open data portal of the Capital City of the Slovak Republic Bratislava,</li>
                        <li>The coordinators communicate with DDPA and Chief Innovation Officer about their data management goals, analytical needs and data procurement intentions.</li>
                    </ol>

                    <h3>Article VI</h3>
                    <h4>Shared Storage and Data Set Standards</h4>
                    <ol>
                        <li>DDPA in cooperation with DMIS, is responsible for managing the shared storage of data sets and the access to the shared storage,</li>
                        <li>Shared storage access can be granted to an employee based on the request of her supervisor. Submitting a request to grant an employee the rights to read or publish data on the shared storage can be made through HelpDesk,</li>
                        <li>The coordinators and responsible organisational bodies are responsible for the timeliness, correctness, and completeness of the data sets shared in the shared storage,</li>
                        <li>In the shared storage, data sets are shared in machine-readable, processable and standardly used formats, especially open formats such as CSV, TXT, XLSX, JSON, XML, GeoJSON and SHP (Act No. 55/2014 Collection of laws of the Slovak Republic). </li>
                        <li>If the data sets to be shared in the shared storage are not saved in standard formats, a coordinator or responsible organisational body consults the sharing with DDPA in advance. DDPA may in special cases allow data sets to be shared in formats other than standard formats.</li>
                        <li>If the data sets to be shared in the shared storage are not saved in standard formats and five years have elapsed since they were created, such data sets are shared in the shared storage without any change in the format. </li>
                        <li>If the size of a separate data set exceeds 500 MB, the data set is shared in a compressed format ZIP, TAR, TAR, GZ (GZIP) without a password.</li>
                    </ol>

                    <h3>Article VII</h3>
                    <h4>Basic Principles of Data Publishing</h4>
                    <ol>
                        <li>Data sets are published on the open data portal in open formats, in accordance with the Act on standards ISVS č. 55/2014 Collection of Laws of the Slovak Republic.</li>
                        <li>Data under the protection of personal data, data containing confidential information or trade secrets, data sets protected by copyright, data sets whose publication is contrary to applicable legislation, data sets whose publication is contrary to the license of the data set and data sets about which the Municipal Office of the Capital City of the Slovak Republic Bratislava has pledged to maintain confidentiality, cannot be published.  </li>
                        <li>Publishing data sets which do not contain information stated in paragraph 2 of this Article is the responsibility of the responsible bodies of the Municipal Office of the Capital City of the Slovak Republic Bratislava. DDPA acts as an advisor and a controller ODPA acts as an advisory and control unit which, at the request of the responsible bodies and at the request of the public, publishes data sets on the open data portal of the Capital City of the Slovak Republic Bratislava.</li>
                        <li>Data sets originating from publicly available sources can be published on the open data portal without an approval of the head of the organisational body to which such data sets thematically belong. DDPA informs the relevant organisational body of their publication. </li>
                    </ol>

                    <h3>Article VIII</h3>
                    <h4>Standards for Published Data Sets on the Open Data Portal</h4>
                    <ol>
                        <li>The responsible bodies are responsible for the completeness and quality of published data sets, so that the content is sufficiently representative. </li>
                        <li>The responsible bodies, together with the published data sets, provide DDPA with metadata that describe or identify items in data sets, as well as the data type and scope, if the format in which the data set is stored requires it.</li>
                        <li>For the purposes of publishing data sets, data sets are forwarded to DDPA in predetermined formats that are machine-readable, processable and standardly used.</li>
                        <li>The correctness of the published data sets is the responsibility of the body that is in charge of the creation and/or management of the data sets. If the anonymization of data sets is required before publication, the responsible body may contact DDPA for cooperation.</li>
                    </ol>

                    <h3>Article IX</h3>
                    <h4>Specific Provisions for the Publication of Data from Internal Applications and Information Systems</h4>
                    <ol>
                        <li>Data sets, which are of internal nature, are not freely shareable and do not fulfil the characteristics of open data, are not subject to publication on the open data portal of the Capital City of the Slovak Republic Bratislava.</li>
                        <li>Data sets of municipal organisations and enterprises can be published on the open data portal in an aggregated form and used for statistical or analytical purposes or after prior discussion with the relevant municipal organization or enterprise in the form of individual data, if the content and character of the data file permits.</li>
                    </ol>

                    <h3>Article X</h3>
                    <h4>Procedure for Publishing Open Data</h4>
                    <ol>
                        <li>The responsible body and DDPA request the publication of open data on the portal via HelpDesk. The request shall specify the category within which the data set is to be published, the size of the data set, the granularity, the period for which the data set is published, the source, the licence and the type of format in which the data set is stored.</li>
                        <li>
                            Depending on the complexity of the request, DDPA can:
                            <ul>
                                <li>publish the data set on the open data portal,</li>
                                <li>ask the responsible body to add information or modify the data set until it is in a form suitable for publication on the portal,</li>
                                <li>reject the publication of the data set, if such a publication would breach provisions of this Directive.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li>DDPA notifies the responsible organisational unit of the release of the data set.</li>
                    </ol>

                    <h3>Article XI</h3>
                    <h4>Specific Provisions for Municipal Organisations and Enterprises</h4>
                    <ol>
                        <li>
                            In order to harmonize processes, collection, creation, management and sharing of data sets in a shared storage, municipal organisations and enterprises are required to:
                            <ul>
                                <li>follow and implement provisions referred to in Article 5 of this Directive,</li>
                                <li>follow and implement provisions referred to in Article 6 of this Directive,</li>
                                <li>follow and implement provisions referred to in Article 12 of this Directive. </li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                    </ol>

                    <h3>Article XII</h3>
                    <h4>Specific Provisions for the Publication of Public Contracts Data </h4>
                    <ol>
                        <li>If a public tender is held within the Municipal Office of Capital City of SR Bratislava, the direct or indirect result of which are data sets and / or data sets are part of the subject of the contract and / or data sets are used to elaborate the subject of the contract, the delivered subject of the contract shall include both source and the resulting data.</li>
                        <li>If a public tender is held within the Municipal Office of Capital City of SR Bratislava, the direct or indirect result of which is an information system containing data sets, the delivered subject of the contract shall include the possibility to publish selected data as open data.</li>
                        <li>It is recommended to insert a text which directly obliges the supplier to provide data sets as a part the contract in the description of the subject of a public procurement contract, e.g. as follows:</li>
                        <br>
                        <span>„As a part of the delivery of the order, we require the provision of both the source and the resulting data sets, including the transfer of the rights referred to in § 135 par. 1 of the Copyright Act and Distribution of Rights. Data will be provided in standard open formats e.g. CSV, TXT, XLSX, JSON or XML or in geoformats GeoJSON, SHP, or other machine-readable and standard formats. “</span>
                    </ol>

                    <h3>Article XIII</h3>
                    <h4>Final Provisions</h4>
                    <ol>
                        <li>This Directive enters into force on the day of its publication. </li>
                    </ol>



